at.tugraz.kmi.medokyservice.fca.lib.colibri.lib

Interface Relation

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HashRelation, HybridRelation, StdRelation, TreeRelation

    public interface Relation
    Representation of a context, i.e. a binary relation between a set of objects and a set of attributes.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Daniel N. Goetzmann

    • Method Detail

      • disallowChanges

        boolean disallowChanges()
        Activates write protection on this relation.

        After this method has been called, this relation shall be unmodifiable, i.e. if there is a call attempting to change the contents of this set, an exception will be thrown. Note that the implementation of this method is optional in classes that implement this interface.

        Returns:
        true iff write protection is activated.

      • getObjects

        java.util.Iterator<java.lang.Comparable> getObjects(java.lang.Comparable attribute)
        Returns an iterator over the objects which have the specified attribute.

        More formally, this method returns an iterator iterating over all objects o for which it is true that the pair (o, attribute) is contained in this relation.

        There are no guarantees concerning the order in which the objects are returned (unless this relation is an instance of a class that provides a guarantee).

        Parameters:
        attribute - the attribute whose objects shall be returned.
        Returns:
        an iterator over the objects of attribute.

      • getAttributes

        java.util.Iterator<java.lang.Comparable> getAttributes(java.lang.Comparable object)

        More formally, this method returns an iterator iterating over all attributes a for which it is true that the pair (object, a) is contained in this relation.

        There are no guarantees concerning the order in which the attributes are returned (unless this relation is an instance of a class that provides a guarantee).

        Parameters:
        object - the object whose objects shall be returned.
        Returns:
        an iterator over the attributes of object.

      • commonObjects

        ComparableSet commonObjects(java.util.Collection<java.lang.Comparable> attributes)
                            throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Returns a set of objects which have all the specified attributes.

        More formally, this method returns a set that contains all objects o for which it is true that for all attributes a that are contained in coll the pair (o, a) is contained in this relation.

        Parameters:
        attributes - a collection of attributes.
        Returns:
        the set of objects that have all the attributes contained in the collection attributes.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if attributes is null one of the elements contained in attributes is not contained in the attribute set of this relation.

      • commonAttributes

        ComparableSet commonAttributes(java.util.Collection<java.lang.Comparable> objects)
                               throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Returns a set of attributes which are associated with all the specified objects.

        More formally, this method returns a set that contains all attributes a for which it is true that for all objects o that are contained in coll the pair (o, a) is contained in this relation.

        Parameters:
        objects - a collection of objects.
        Returns:
        the set of attributes all objects contained in the collection objects have.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if objects is null or one of the elements contained in objects is not contained in the object set of this relation.

      • add

        void add(java.lang.Comparable object,
       java.lang.Comparable attribute)
         throws java.lang.ClassCastException,
                java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
        Adds the pair (object, attribute) to this relation.

        If object is not yet contained in the object set of this relation it will be added to that set. Similarly, if attribute is not yet contained in the attribute set of this relation it will be added to that set.

        If object is null no pair will be added to this relation but attribute will be added to the attribute set of this relation. Similarly, if attribute is null no pair will be added to this relation but object will be added to the object set of this relation.

        Parameters:
        object - the object. If this is null, only the attribute will be added to the attribute set.
        attribute - the attribute. If this is null, only the object will be added to the object set
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassCastException - if object is not mutually comparable with the objects contained in the object set of this relation or attribute is not mutually comparable with the attributes contained in the attribute set of this relation.
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if this relation is write protected.

      • remove

        void remove(java.lang.Comparable object,
          java.lang.Comparable attribute)
            throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
        Removes the pair (object, attribute) from this relation.

        If object is null then attribute will be removed from the attribute set of this relation and all pairs whose attribute is attribute will be removed from this relation. Similarly, if attribute is null then object will be removed from the attribute set of this relation and all pairs whose object is object will be removed from this relation.

        Parameters:
        object - the object.
        attribute - the attribute.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if this relation is write protected.

      • contains

        boolean contains(java.lang.Object object,
               java.lang.Object attribute)
        Returns true if and only if the pair (object, attribute) is contained in this relation.

        If object is null this method will return true if and only if attribute is contained in the attribute set of this relation. Similarly, if attribute is null this method will return true if and only if object is contained in the object set of this relation.

        Parameters:
        object - the object.
        attribute - the attribute.
        Returns:
        true, iff the pair (object, attribute) is contained in the relation.
